<section xml:id="sec-mertens" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Mertens' Theorems</title>
  
  <theorem>
  <title>Mertens' Theorem</title>
  <statement>
  For <m>x \geq 2</m> we have
  <mdn>
  <mrow> \sum_{n \leq x} \frac{\Lambda(n)}{n} \amp = \log x + O(1) </mrow>,
  <mrow> \sum_{p \leq x} \frac{\log p}{p} \amp = \log x + O(1) </mrow>,
  <mrow> \sum_{p \leq x} \frac{1}{p} \amp = \log \log x + b + O\left(\frac{1}{\log x}\right) </mrow>,
  <mrow> \prod_{p \leq x} \left( 1 - \frac{1}{p} \right)^{-1} \amp = e^c \log x + O(1) </mrow>,
  <mrow> \prod_{p \leq x} \left( 1 - \frac{1}{p} \right) \amp = \frac{e^{-c}}{\log x} + O\left( \frac{1}{(\log x)^2} \right) </mrow>,
  </mdn>
  where <m>b</m> and <m>c</m> are constants.
  In fact <m>c = \gamma</m> is the Euler-Mascheroni constant.
  </statement>
  
  </theorem>
 
 
 

</section>